🌳 ReGen Mapper
AI-powered platform for visualizing and coordinating reforestation efforts. Built for the Land ReGen Hackathon to support SDG 15: Life on Land.

📌 Overview
ReGen Mapper empowers communities, NGOs, and schools to plan, track, and showcase reforestation initiatives using geospatial data, AI insights, and transparent impact metrics.

🎯 Objectives
Map reforestation zones using GIS and satellite data

Log tree planting activities with species, dates, and contributors

Suggest optimal restoration zones using AI

Visualize impact: tree count, CO₂ offset, SDG alignment

Provide onboarding flows for local changemakers

🧩 Core Features (MVP Scope)
Feature Description
🌍 Interactive Map Zoomable map with overlays for restoration zones and tree density
🌱 Planting Log Form to record tree species, planting date, and contributor info
🧠 AI Restoration Planner Suggests planting zones based on soil, rainfall, and vegetation data
📊 Impact Dashboard Displays metrics like total trees, CO₂ offset, and SDG 15 progress
🛠️ Admin Panel (Optional) For managing contributors, zones, and campaign visibility
⚙️ Tech Stack
Frontend: React · Bootstrap · Mapbox or Leaflet

Backend: Flask · Supabase or Railway (MongoDB)

AI Tools: Claude.ai · Bolt.new

Geospatial APIs: Sentinel Hub · OpenStreetMap · GIS APIs

Deployment: Railway (Free Tier) · GitHub Codespaces

🧪 Requirements Breakdown
Module Requirements
Map Integration GIS API access, map rendering library, zone overlay logic
Data Storage Tree logs, contributor profiles, zone metadata
AI Suggestions Access to soil/rainfall/vegetation datasets, prompt engineering
UI/UX Responsive layout, onboarding clarity, nature-inspired design
Impact Metrics CO₂ offset formulas, SDG mapping logic, dashboard components
Security & Scaling Environment variables, modular folder structure, onboarding documentation
